    <item>
      <title>NPCT DBT 2025: Benefits, Purpose, and Complete Guide</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/bank/dbt-aadhar-linking-with-npci/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2025 13:04:33 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/bank/dbt-aadhar-linking-with-npci/</guid>
      <description>NPCT DBT (National Payments Corporation of India – Direct Benefit Transfer) enables the Indian government to transfer subsidies, pensions, scholarships, and other benefits directly to beneficiaries’ bank accounts. It ensures fast, secure, and transparent payments by linking beneficiaries’ Aadhaar numbers with their bank accounts. Payments can be tracked via bank statements, the DBT Bharat Portal, or the UMANG app. This system covers various schemes such as LPG subsidies, MGNREGA wages, farmer support, pensions, and student scholarships.</description>
    </item>
